{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-01930/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-01930"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:19:30"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["establishing shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A plain dress form stands in a designer's workshop."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-01930","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-01930"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/canvas/1/c394a565-8044-4090-9d84-703dbf24a0df","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T15:16:11.783Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>According to set decorator Véronique Melery, Owlpen Manor already told “too much of a story” with all its items, so the crew’s task was to “strip the house of a lot of personal items and furniture, then redress with our own...trying to be almost as good as what was already existing, and matching the two choices to make them merge in a believable world of <em>Woodcock</em> [italics in original]... The wooden worktable was made of solid pieces from an oak tree cut on the property of Owlpen. His ruler is inlaid on the side of the table. He has a well organized workplace: a corner to draw, a corner to rest and think, a corner to sew on his old machine, a corner to dress his muses in front of a large mirror, and a large table to cut and assemble patterns” (Burg, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW27346759 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.setdecorators.org/?art=film_decor_features&amp;SHOW=SetDecor_Film_Phantom_Thread\"><u>Set Decore</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01930/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:460.35242290748903,792.7092511013216,1148.3480176211453,202.81938325991177"}}}]}]}]}